        "Answer": "a. P700,000. The basis of the property in the hands of the donee is the carry-over basis (Sec. 40(B)(3), NIRC). b. The old car is a capital asset. It is property held by the taxpayer, but is not stock in trade of the taxpayer or other property of a kind which would properly be included in the inventory of the taxpayer if on hand at the close of the taxable year, or property held by the taxpayer primarily for sale to customers in the ordinary course of his trade or business, or property used in the trade or business, of a character which is subject to the allowance for depreciation; or real property used in trade or business of the taxpayer (Sec. 39, NIRC). c. YES. Capital gain is P100,000. The amount of the taxable gain is subject to the holding period of the asset (Sec. 39,NIRC)."
