        "Question": "Spouses Pablo Gonzales and Teresita Gonzales, both resident citizens acquire during their marriage a residential house and lot located in Makati City. The property is registered in the name of Pablo. The spouses have no children. On April 10, 2010, Pablo died. The property was then transferred to Teresita as the sole heir. During the year 2010, the property earned P500,000.00 in rentals. The income and expenses of the property for the year 2010 are as follows: Gross rentals - P500,000.00; Real property tax - P50,000.00; and Insurance premium - P10,000.00.  a. Is Mr. Pablo Gonzales required to file income tax for 2010? If so, how much income must he declare for the year? How much personal and additional exemption is he entitled to? Explain your answer. b. Is Mrs. Teresita Gonzales required to file income tax return for 2010? If so, how much income must she declare for the year? How much personal exemption is she entitled to? Explain your answer. c. Is the Estate of the late Pablo Gonzales required to file income tax return for 2010? If so, how much income must it declare for the year? How much personal exemption is it entitled to? Explain your answer.",
